011/david-beckham-do-something-athlete-award-winner-533638 |url-status=dead |archivedate=3 October 2011 |title=David Beckham: Do Something Athlete Award Winner! |accessdate=12 June 2012 }}</ref>\n*A.C. Milan Hall of Fame<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/david-beckham|title=A.C. Milan Hall of Fame: David Beckham|publisher=A.C. Milan|accessdate=12 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Records===\n*First Englishman to win league titles in four countries (England, Spain, United States, France).<ref name=\"honours\"/>\n*First England player to score at three [[FIFA World Cup]]s.<ref name=\"honours\"/>\n*First British footballer to play 100 [[UEFA Champions League]] games.<ref name=\"honours\"/>\n*Seventh in the [[Premier League]]'s [[Premier League records and statistics#Assists|all time assist provider chart]], with 80 assists in 265 appearances.<ref name=\"PL-assists\">{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/stats/top/players/goal_assist|title=Premier League Player Stats: Assists \u2013 All Seasons|publisher=Premier League|accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.premiersoccerstats.com/Records.cfm?DOrderby=Ass&DYearby=All%20Seasons |title=All Time Player Records |publisher=Premiersoccerstats.com |date=13 August 2010 |accessdate=21 January 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131204174344/http://www.premiersoccerstats.com/Records.cfm?DOrderby=Ass&DYearby=All%20Seasons |archivedate=4 December 2013  }}</ref>\n*Fourth highest number of games as captain of the [[England national football team]]: 59.<ref name=\"Beckham stands down\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://englandfootballonline.com/TeamCapt/CaptBio/CaptBeckhamDRJ.html|title=David Beckham - Captain Statistics|access-date=5 November 2019|date=1 May 2011}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Association football|English football}}\n*[[Beckham rule]]\n*[[List of footballers with more than 100 international caps]]\n*[[List of professional sports team owners]]\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n\n===Books===\n* {{Cite book |last1=Beckham |first1=David |title=David Beckham: My Side |publisher=HarperCollinsWillow |year=2002 |isbn=978-0-00-715732-7 }}\n* {{Cite book |last1=Beckham |first1=David |last2=Freeman |first2=Dean |title=Beckham: My World |publisher=Hodder & Stoughton |year=2001 |isbn=978-0-340-79270-4 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/beckhammyworld0000beck_i7u3 }}\n* {{Cite book |last1=Beckham |first1=David |last2=Watt |first2=Tom |title=Beckham: Both Feet on the Ground |publisher=HarperCollins |year=2003 |isbn=978-0-06-057093-4 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/beckhambothfeeto00beck }}\n* {{Cite book |last=Crick |first=Michael |title=The Boss \u2013 The Many Sides of Alex Ferguson |publisher=Pocket Books |year=2003 |isbn=978-0-7434-2991-7 |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/bossmanysidesofa0000cric }}\n* {{Cite book |last1=Ferguson |first1=Alex |last2=McIlvanney |first2=Hugh |title=Managing My Life \u2013 My Autobiography |publisher=Hodder & Stoughton |year=1999 |isbn=978-0-340-72855-0 |url=https://archive.org/details/managingmylife00alex }}\n* {{Cite book |last=Wahl |first=Grant |title=The Beckham Experiment: How the World's Most Famous Athlete Tried to Conquer America |publisher=Crown |year=2009 |isbn=978-0-307-40859-4 }}\n\n===Internet===\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n*{{cite magazine|first=Grant|last=Wahl|title=Beckham's Last Stand: In the fifth and final year of his MLS contract, he's back at the top of his game at last. Now, as the 2011 playoffs begin, he and the Galaxy look to stamp his American experiment a success by winning a championship|date=31 October 2011|magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]]|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1191594/index.htm |accessdate=28 October 2011 |quote='In [Major League Soccer] his ability to hold the ball in that position and pass makes him unique,' says [coach Bruce] Arena. 'He's right in the middle of things. In every game, he touches the ball the most of any player.'}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|David Beckham}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{FIFA player}}\n* {{UEFA player}}\n* {{NFT player}}\n* [http://www.realmadrid.com/en/about-real-madrid/history/football-legends/david-robert-joseph-beckham David Beckham] at [[Real Madrid|RealMadrid.com]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110115035646/http://www.manutd.com/en/Players-And-Staff/Legends/David-Beckham.aspx David Beckham] at ManUtd.com\n* {{MLS player}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n* {{englandstats|id=96}}\n\n{{Inter Miami CF}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title=England squads\n|bg=white\n|fg=#0B0B3F\n|bordercolor=#0B0B3F\n|list1=\n{{England squad 1998 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{England squad UEFA Euro 2000}}\n{{England squad 2002 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{England squad UEFA Euro 2004}}\n{{England squad 2006 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n|bg=gold\n|fg=navy\n|title=Awards\n|list1=\n{{1996\u201397 FA Premier League PFA Team of the Year}}\n{{1997\u201398 FA Premier League PFA Team of the Year}}\n{{1998\u201399 FA Premier League PFA Team of the Year}}\n{{1999\u20132000 FA Premier League PFA Team of the Year}}\n{{PFA Young Player of the Year}}\n{{UEFA Club Footballer of the Year}}\n{{UEFA Club Football Awards}}\n{{ESPY Best MLS Player}}\n{{2001 UEFA Team of the Year}}\n{{2003 UEFA Team of the Year}}\n{{MLS Comeback Player of the Year}}\n{{Sir Matt Busby Player of the Year}}\n{{England Player of the Year}}\n{{FIFA 100}}\n{{BBC Sports Personality of the Year winners}}\n{{2011 MLS Best XI}}\n{{FWA Tribute Award}}\n{{UEFA President's Award}}\n{{English Football Hall of Fame}}\n}}\n{{England 2018}}\n{{Victoria Beckham}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Beckham, David}}\n[[Category:David Beckham| ]]\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English people of Jewish descent]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Leytonstone]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association foo