g-athlete-award-winner-533638 |url-status=dead |archivedate=3 October 2011 |title=David Beckham: Do Something Athlete Award Winner! |accessdate=12 June 2012 }}</ref>\n*A.C. Milan Hall of Fame<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/david-beckham|title=A.C. Milan Hall of Fame: David Beckham|publisher=A.C. Milan|accessdate=12 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Records===\n*First Englishman to win league titles in four countries (England, Spain, United States, France).<ref name=\"honours\"/>\n*First England player to score at three [[FIFA World Cup]]s.<ref name=\"honours\"/>\n*First British footballer to play 100 [[UEFA Champions League]] games.<ref name=\"honours\"/>\n*Seventh in the [[Premier League]]'s [[Premier League records and statistics#Assists|all time assist provider chart]], with 80 assists in 265 appearances.<ref name=\"PL-assists\">{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/stats/top/players/goal_assist|title=Premier League Player Stats: Assists \u2013 All Seasons|publisher=Premier League|accessdate=26 April 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.premiersoccerstats.com/Records.cfm?DOrderby=Ass&DYearby=All%20Seasons |title=All Time Player Records |publisher=Premiersoccerstats.com |date=13 August 2010 |accessdate=21 January 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131204174344/http://www.premiersoccerstats.com/Records.cfm?DOrderby=Ass&DYearby=All%20Seasons |archivedate=4 December 2013  }}</ref>\n*Fourth highest number of games as captain of the [[England national football team]]: 59.<ref name=\"Beckham stands down\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://englandfootballonline.com/TeamCapt/CaptBio/CaptBeckhamDRJ.html|title=David Beckham - Captain Statistics|access-date=5 November 2019|date=1 May 2011}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Association football|English football}}\n*[[Beckham rule]]\n*[[List of footballers with more than 100 international caps]]\n*[[List of professional sports team owners]]\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n\n===Books===\n* 