qua]],  French businessman and politician, [[Minister of the Interior (France)|French Minister of the Interior]] (d. 2015)\n*[[1928]] &ndash; [[Karl Josef Becker]], German cardinal and theologian (d. 2015)\n*  1928   &ndash; [[Otto Piene]], German sculptor and academic (d. 2014)\n*[[1929]] &ndash; [[Peter Hordern]], English soldier and politician\n*[[1930]] &ndash; [[Clive Revill]], New Zealand actor and singer\n*[[1931]] &ndash; [[Bill Miles]], American director and producer (d. 2013)\n*[[1934]] &ndash; [[James Drury]], American actor (d. 2020)\n*  1934   &ndash; [[George Shirley]], African-American tenor and educator\n*[[1935]] &ndash; [[Brian Clay]], Australian rugby league player (d. 1987)\n*  1935   &ndash; [[Costas Ferris]], Egyptian-Greek actor, director, producer, and screenwriter\n*[[1936]] &ndash; [[Roger Graef]], American-English criminologist, director, and producer\n*  1936   &ndash; [[Vladimir H\u00fctt]], Estonian physicist and philosopher (d. 1997)\n*  1936   &ndash; [[Tommy Ivo|\"TV\" Tommy Ivo]], American actor and [[Drag racing|drag racer]]\n*[[1937]] &ndash; [[Jan Kaplick\u00fd]], Czech architect, designed the [[Selfridges Building, Birmingham|Selfridges Building]] (d. 2009)\n*  1937   &ndash; [[Tatyana Shchelkanova]], Russian long jumper and heptathlete (d. 2011)\n*  1937   &ndash; [[Teddy Taylor]], Scottish journalist and politician, [[Shadow Secretary of State for Scotland]]\n*[[1939]] &ndash; [[Glen Hardin]],  American pianist and arranger\n*  1939   &ndash; [[Thomas J. Moyer]], American lawyer and judge (d. 2010)\n*[[1940]] &ndash; [[Joseph L. Goldstein]], American biochemist and geneticist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate\n*  1940   &ndash; [[Mike Vickers]], English guitarist, saxophonist, and songwriter \n*[[1941]] &ndash; [[Michael D. Higgins]], Irish sociologist and politician, 9th [[President of Ireland]]\n*[[1942]] &ndash; [[Michael Beloff]], English lawyer and academic\n*  1942   &ndash; [[Steve Blass]],