us thrower (d. 1944)\n*[[1897]] &ndash; [[Ardito Desio]], Italian geologist and cartographer (d. 2001)\n*  1897   &ndash; [[Per-Erik Hedlund]], Swedish skier (d. 1975)\n*[[1898]] &ndash; [[Patrick Hennessy (industrialist)|Patrick Hennessy]], Irish soldier and businessman (d. 1981)\n*[[1900]] &ndash; [[Bertha Isaacs]], Bahamian teacher, tennis player, politician and women's rights activist (d. 1997)<ref>{{cite web|ref={{harvid|Womens Suffrage Bahamas|2012}}|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|title=Albertha Isaacs|url=http://www.womensuffragebahamas.com/history/suffrage-women/albertha-isaacs/|website=Womens Suffrage Bahamas|accessdate=3 February 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160515194411/http://www.womensuffragebahamas.com/history/suffrage-women/albertha-isaacs/|archivedate=17 October 2017|location=Nassau, The Bahamas|date=2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n*[[1901]] &ndash; [[Al Lewis (lyricist)|Al Lewis]], American songwriter (d. 1967)\n*  1901   &ndash; [[L\u00e1szl\u00f3 N\u00e9meth]], Hungarian dentist, author, and playwright (d. 1975)\n*[[1902]] &ndash; [[Waldemar Hammenh\u00f6g]], Swedish author (d. 1972)\n*  1902   &ndash; [[Giuseppe Pella]], Italian politician, 32nd [[Prime Minister of Italy]] (d. 1981)\n*[[1904]] &ndash; [[Pigmeat Markham]], African-American comedian, singer, and dancer (d. 1981)\n*[[1905]] &ndash; [[Sydney Halter]], Canadian lawyer and businessman (d. 1990)\n*  1905   &ndash; [[George H. Hitchings]], American physician and pharmacologist, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate (d. 1998)\n*[[1907]] &ndash; [[Mikl\u00f3s R\u00f3zsa]], Hungarian-American composer and conductor (d. 1995)\n*[[1911]] &ndash; [[Ilario Bandini]], Italian businessman and racing driver (d. 1992)\n*  1911   &ndash; [[Maurice Goldhaber]], Ukrainian Jewish-American physicist and academic (d. 2011)\n*[[1914]] &ndash; [[Claire Martin (writer)|Claire Martin]], Canadian author (d. 2014)\n*[[1915]] &ndash; [[Joy Davidman]], Polish-U