{{cite web|title=Train Station Patronage FY2008-2014|url=https://www.ptv.vic.gov.au/assets/PTV/PTV%20docs/research/PTV-Station-by-Station-Fact-Sheet-accessible-version-2015.xls|publisher=Public Transport Victoria|access-date=1 November 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160330211628/https://www.ptv.vic.gov.au/assets/PTV/PTV%20docs/research/PTV-Station-by-Station-Fact-Sheet-accessible-version-2015.xls|archive-date=30 March 2016|url-status=dead|format=XLS|date=14 May 2015|df=dmy-all}} (access from [https://www.ptv.vic.gov.au/about-ptv/ptv-data-and-reports/research-and-statistics/] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103220141/https://www.ptv.vic.gov.au/about-ptv/ptv-data-and-reports/research-and-statistics/ |date=3 November 2016 }})</ref>|pass_year = 2008\u20132009}}\n{{Rail pass box|passengers = 706,461<ref name=\"patronage2008-2014\" />|pass_year = 2009\u20132010|pass_percent = 7.06}}\n{{Rail pass box|passengers = 738,349<ref name=\"patronage2008-2014\" />|pass_year = 2010\u20132011|pass_percent = 4.51}}\n{{Rail pass box|passengers = 714,059<ref name=\"patronage2008-2014\" />|pass_year = 2011\u20132012|pass_percent = -3.29}}\n{{Rail pass box|passengers = Not measured<ref name=\"patronage2008-2014\" />|pass_year = 2012\u20132013}}\n{{Rail pass box|passengers = 612,964<ref name=\"patronage2008-2014\" />|pass_year = 2013\u20132014|pass_percent = -14.16}}\n\n| services             = {{s-rail|title=Metro Trains}}\n{{s-line|system=Victoria|line=Pakenham|previous=Dandenong|next=Narre Warren}}\n| services_collapsible = \n| services_state       = \n| other_services_header = Closed station navigation\n| other_services       = {{s-rail|title=Disused}}\n{{rail line|col={{Victoria color|closed}}|route=[[Orbost railway line|Orbost line]]|previous={{stnlnk|General Motors}}|next=''Line open''}}\n| other_services_collapsible = yes\n| other_services_state = \n| embedded             = \n}}\n\n'''Hallam railway station''' is a [[railway station]] located on the [[Gippsland railway line|Gippsland line]], in [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Australia]]. It serves the south-eastern [[Melbourne]] suburb of [[Hallam, Victoria|Hallam]], and opened on 1 December 1880 as '''Hallam's Road'''. It was renamed Hallam on 2 May 1904.<ref>[http://www.vicsig.net/infrastructure/location/Hallam Hallam] Vicsig</ref>\n\nBoom barriers were provided at the Hallam South Road level crossing in 1984.<ref>{{cite magazine|date=September 1983|title=Works|magazine=Newsrail|publisher=Australian Railway Historical Society|page=246}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 July 1990, the station officially operated for passenger business only.<ref name=\"newsrailnov90\">{{cite magazine|date=November 1990|title=Works|magazine=Newsrail|publisher=Australian Railway Historical Society|page=348}}</ref>\n\n==Platforms & services==\nHallam has two side platforms. It is serviced by [[Metro Trains Melbourne|Metro Trains]]' [[Pakenham railway line|Pakenham line]] services.<ref>{{cite PTV route|Pakenham|mode=train}}</ref>\n\n'''Platform 1:'''\n*'''[[Pakenham railway line|Pakenham line]]''': all stations and limited express services to [[Flinders Street railway station|Flinders Street]]\n\n'''Platform 2:'''\n*'''[[Pakenham railway line|Pakenham line]]''': all stations services to [[Pakenham railway station|Pakenham]]\n\nIt is planned to connect the Pakenham line to the [[Sunbury railway line, Melbourne|Sunbury line]] through the new [[Metro Tunnel]] in late 2025.\n\n==Transport links==\n[[Ventura Bus Lines]] and [[Cranbourne Transit]] operates five routes via Hallam station:\n*863: Hampton Park shopping centre - Endeavour Hills shopping centre<ref>{{cite PTV route|863}}</ref>\n*891: [[Lynbrook railway station|Lynbrook station]] \u2013 [[Westfield Fountain Gate]]<ref>{{cite PTV route|891}}</ref>\n*893: [[Cranbourne, Victoria|Cranbourne]] \u2013 [[Dandenong railway station|Dandenong station]]<ref>{{cite PTV route|893}}</ref>\n*894: to Amberley Park ([[Hampton Park, Victoria|Hampton Park]])<ref>{{cite PTV route|894}}</ref>\n*[[Night Network (Melbourne)#Night Bus|{{color box|#000039|{{Font color|white|Night}} {{Font color|#FFA500|Bus}}}}]] 982: Dandenong station \u2013 Cranbourne (Saturday and Sunday mornings only)<ref>{{cite PTV route|982}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.street-directory.com.au/sd3/map.php?x=145.26954000478236&y=-38.01776615139515&l=13&mt=4 Melway map] at street-directory.com.au\n\n{{Public Transport Victoria railway stations|Pakenham=y|state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:Railway stations in Melbourne]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1880]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Railway station in Melbourne, Australia}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2015}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name                 = Hallam\n| type                 = [[Public Transport Victoria|PTV]] [[commuter rail]] station\n| style                = Melbourne\n| image                = Hallam Railway Station, Melbourne.JPG\n| caption              = View of platforms at Hallam, April 2015\n| address              = Hallam Road<br />[[Hallam, Victoria|Hallam]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]] 3803\n| country              = [[Australia]]\n| coordinates          = {{Coord|display=inline,title|-38.0179|145.2702|format=dms|type:railwaystation_region:AU-VIC}}\n| owned                = [[VicTrack]]\n| operator             = [[Metro Trains Melbourne|Metro Trains]]\n| line                 = [[Gippsland railway line|Gippsland line]]\n| distance             = 37.45 kilometres from [[Southern Cross railway station|Southern Cross]]\n| platforms            = 2\n| tracks               = 2\n| train_operators      = [[Metro Trains Melbourne|Metro Trains]]\n| connections          = 5 [[Buses in Melbourne|bus]] routes\n| structure            = At-grade\n| depth                = \n| levels               = \n| parking              = 590 spaces\n| bicycle              = Available\n| disabled    